result.name: Cafe Hay Fever

reviews.text:
The coffee was good, and the cafe itself was quite relaxing, which is nice. Unfortunately the floor really needed a good mopping, and it would have been nice if our order came at the same time, instead of 15 minutes apart. 

The fact that it was still a 4 star experience tells you how good the coffee is.

I wish I had more room to try the lemonade. Oh well maybe next time.

Nice environment - Especially the floral and green decorations.

Hay Fever is located inside Eslite and it is one of the best places to do some reading!
One thing to be aware is there is no wi-fi so let’s just focus on reading your book / chatting with friends:)

The black coffee is more concentrated (and bitter) compared to other cafes. But I like the aroma.

A hybrid of floral shop and cafe and specialty coffee in a mega book store of a modern mall. I've visited their floral shop cafe in the floral street of Princess Edward road and love the decor and hand drip, but it is a bit far for me and bit crowded with shoppers.  Eslite is still missing a specialty coffee shop.  This branch in Causeway Bay is certainly a good addition to Eslite store.  Accepted Octopus and credit cards.

reviews.author_name: A T M O S P H Y X
reviews.text: The atmosphere is one of the best in Causeway Bay. The food tastes a bit plain but their drink selection is lovely. They serve salads, sandwiches and pasta. A good place for coffee and getting away from the hustle busle.

Good place for serious coffee lovers, plus a variety of light food. 
A scent of dried flowers and its location at a renowned bookshop make Hay Fever even more popular.
